{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876455449,"sessionID":"ses_285850964ffey2ZpSGUQcIATeP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7c36a10014tk6e1X4uZladm","messageID":"msg_d7a7c2922001oWX4AMXbXb7DA7","sessionID":"ses_285850964ffey2ZpSGUQcIATeP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e1d7bb5c9cd2472b82fb9b4aa9e3d7dd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Implementation Summary: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document summarizes the complete implementation of the K8s/AgentCube Provider system for the AgentCube CLI project, following the specifications in `proposal.md`.\n6: \n7: ## Implemented Components\n8: \n9: ### 1. Provider Base Interface (`agentcube/providers/base.py`)\n10: \n11: **Classes and Enums:**\n12: - `ProviderStatus` - Enumeration of provider states (pending, deploying, running, failed, not_found, error)\n13: - `DeploymentResult` - Dataclass for deployment operation results with `to_dict()` method\n14: - `AgentStatus` - Dataclass for agent status information with `to_dict()` method\n15: - `BaseProvider` - Abstract base class defining the provider interface\n16: \n17: **Key Methods:**\n18: - `deploy(agent_name, image_url, port, **kwargs)` - Deploy an agent\n19: - `get_status(agent_name)` - Get agent status\n20: - `delete(agent_name)` - Delete an agent\n21: - `get_provider_type()` - Get provider type identifier\n22: - `validate_config(**kwargs)` - Validate configuration parameters\n23: - `_sanitize_name(name)` - Sanitize names for Kubernetes compliance\n24: - `_load_kubernetes_config()` - Load Kubernetes configuration\n25: - `_ensure_namespace()` - Ensure namespace exists\n26: \n27: ### 2. Custom Exceptions (`agentcube/providers/exceptions.py`)\n28: \n29: **Exception Classes:**\n30: - `ProviderError` - Base exception for all provider errors\n31: - `ProviderConfigurationError` - Configuration validation errors\n32: - `ProviderDeploymentError` - Deployment operation errors\n33: - `ProviderTimeoutError` - Operation timeout errors\n34: - `ProviderNotFoundError` - Resource not found errors\n35: \n36: ### 3. Retry Mechanism (`agentcube/providers/retry.py`)\n37: \n38: **Components:**\n39: - `retry_on_exception` - Decorator for automatic retry with exponential backoff\n40:   - Configurable max attempts, delay, backoff factor, and exception types\n41:   - Logs retry attempts and failures\n42: - `RetryableOperation` - Context manager for retryable operations\n43:   - Built-in timeout support\n44:   - Automatic retry with configurable parameters\n45: \n46: ### 4. KubernetesProvider (`agentcube/providers/k8s_provider.py`)\n47: \n48: **Refactored with unified interface:**\n49: - Implements `BaseProvider` interface\n50: - Uses standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service\n51: - Supports configuration validation (replicas, node_port)\n52: - Implements retry mechanism for deployment readiness check\n53: - Returns structured `DeploymentResult` and `AgentStatus` objects\n54: \n55: **Key Features:**\n56: - Automatic namespace creation\n57: - Name sanitization for Kubernetes compliance\n58: - Retry-based deployment readiness check\n59: - Graceful error handling with detailed error messages\n60: \n61: ### 5. AgentCubeProvider (`agentcube/providers/agentcube_provider.py`)\n62: \n63: **Refactored with unified interface:**\n64: - Implements `BaseProvider` interface\n65: - Uses AgentRuntime Custom Resource (CRD: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1)\n66: - Supports configuration validation (workload_manager_url, router_url)\n67: - Returns structured `DeploymentResult` and `AgentStatus` objects\n68: \n69: **Key Features:**\n70: - Automatic namespace creation\n71: - CR creation or update (idempotent operations)\n72: - Environment variable support for required URLs\n73: - Comprehensive error handling\n74: \n75: ### 6. Provider Factory (`agentcube/providers/factory.py`)\n76: \n77: **Class:** `ProviderFactory`\n78: \n79: **Methods:**\n80: - `register(provider_type, provider_class)` - Register a provider class\n81: - `unregister(provider_type)` - Unregister a provider class\n82: - `create(provider_type, **kwargs)` - Create provider instance\n83: - `list_providers()` - List all registered providers\n84: - `is_registered(provider_type)` - Check if provider is registered\n85: \n86: **Default Providers:**\n87: - `k8s` - KubernetesProvider\n88: - `agentcube` - AgentCubeProvider\n89: \n90: ### 7. Status Monitoring (`agentcube/providers/monitoring.py`)\n91: \n92: **Classes:**\n93: - `StatusMonitor` - Monitor agent status with polling\n94:   - `monitor(duration, callback)` - Monitor for specified duration\n95:   - `wait_for_status(target_status, timeout)` - Wait for target status\n96:   - `stop()` - Stop monitoring\n97: - `EventMonitor` - Monitor Kubernetes events and pod logs\n98:   - `get_events(since)` - Get Kubernetes events\n99:   - `get_pod_logs(container_name, tail_lines)` - Get pod logs\n100: \n101: ### 8. Configuration Validator (`agentcube/providers/config_validator.py`)\n102: \n103: **Class:** `ConfigValidator`\n104: \n105: **Static Methods:**\n106: - `validate_provider_config(provider_type, **kwargs)` - Validate specific provider config\n107: - `validate_k8s_config(replicas, node_port)` - Validate Kubernetes config\n108: - `validate_agentcube_config(workload_manager_url, router_url)` - Validate AgentCube config\n109: - `validate_common_config(namespace, kubeconfig, timeout)` - Validate common config\n110: - `validate_all_configs(provider_type, **kwargs)` - Validate all configs\n111: \n112: ### 9. Configuration Manager (`agentcube/providers/config_manager.py`)\n113: \n114: **Class:** `ProviderConfigManager`\n115: \n116: **Features:**\n117: - YAML-based configuration persistence\n118: - Default config file: `~/.agentcube/providers.yaml`\n119: - Configuration per provider type\n120: \n121: **Methods:**\n122: - `get_config(provider_type, key, default)` - Get config value\n123: - `set_config(provider_type, key, value)` - Set config value\n124: - `remove_config(provider_type, key)` - Remove config value\n125: - `get_provider_kwargs(provider_type)` - Get provider initialization parameters\n126: - `clear_provider_config(provider_type)` - Clear all provider config\n127: - `list_providers()` - List providers with config\n128: - `export_config()` - Export all configuration\n129: - `import_config(config)` - Import configuration\n130: \n131: ### 10. Plugin System (`agentcube/providers/plugins.py`)\n132: \n133: **Classes:**\n134: - `ProviderPlugin` - Abstract base class for provider plugins\n135:   - `name` - Plugin name property\n136:   - `provider_type` - Provider type property\n137:   - `create_provider(**kwargs)` - Create provider instance\n138:   - `validate_config(**kwargs)` - Validate plugin config\n139:   - `initialize()` - Plugin initialization hook\n140:   - `cleanup()` - Plugin cleanup hook\n141: - `ProviderPluginManager` - Manager for provider plugins\n142:   - `register_plugin(plugin)` - Register a plugin\n143:   - `unregister_plugin(plugin_name)` - Unregister a plugin\n144:   - `get_plugin(plugin_name)` - Get plugin by name\n145:   - `list_plugins()` - List all plugins\n146:   - `has_plugin(plugin_name)` - Check if plugin exists\n147:   - `reload_plugin(plugin_name)` - Reload a plugin\n148: \n149: **Global Instance:** `plugin_manager` - Default plugin manager instance\n150: \n151: ### 11. Package Exports (`agentcube/providers/__init__.py`)\n152: \n153: Exports all provider components for easy import:\n154: - Base classes and data structures\n155: - Exception classes\n156: - Provider factory\n157: - Concrete providers\n158: - Retry mechanisms\n159: - Monitoring utilities\n160: - Configuration tools\n161: - Plugin system\n162: \n163: ## Unit Tests\n164: \n165: Comprehensive unit tests created for all components:\n166: \n167: 1. `tests/test_providers_base.py` - Tests for base module\n168: 2. `tests/test_providers_exceptions.py` - Tests for exception classes\n169: 3. `tests/test_providers_retry.py` - Tests for retry mechanisms\n170: 4. `tests/test_providers_factory.py` - Tests for provider factory\n171: 5. `tests/test_providers_config_validator.py` - Tests for config validator\n172: \n173: ## Architecture Benefits\n174: \n175: 1. **Unified Interface** - All providers implement the same base interface\n176: 2. **Extensibility** - Plugin system allows adding custom providers\n177: 3. **Type Safety** - Dataclasses for structured data with type hints\n178: 4. **Error Handling** - Comprehensive custom exception hierarchy\n179: 5. **Retry Logic** - Built-in retry mechanism for resilience\n180: 6. **Configuration Management** - Centralized config validation and persistence\n181: 7. **Monitoring** - Real-time status and event monitoring capabilities\n182: 8. **Testing** - High test coverage with comprehensive unit tests\n183: \n184: ## File Structure\n185: \n186: ```\n187: agentcube/providers/\n188: ├── __init__.py                 # Package exports\n189: ├── base.py                     # Base interface and data structures\n190: ├── exceptions.py               # Custom exceptions\n191: ├── retry.py                    # Retry mechanisms\n192: ├── factory.py                  # Provider factory\n193: ├── k8s_provider.py             # Kubernetes provider\n194: ├── agentcube_provider.py       # AgentCube provider\n195: ├── monitoring.py               # Status and event monitoring\n196: ├── config_validator.py         # Configuration validation\n197: ├── config_manager.py           # Configuration management\n198: └── plugins.py                  # Plugin system\n199: \n200: tests/\n201: ├── test_providers_base.py              # Base module tests\n202: ├── test_providers_exceptions.py        # Exception tests\n203: ├── test_providers_retry.py             # Retry tests\n204: ├── test_providers_factory.py           # Factory tests\n205: └── test_providers_config_validator.py  # Config validator tests\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ## Notes\n209: \n210: - All code follows Python best practices with proper type hints\n211: - Comprehensive docstrings for all public APIs\n212: - Error handling with detailed error messages\n213: - Logging integration for debugging and monitoring\n214: - Clean separation of concerns between components\n215: - Easy to extend with new providers or functionality\n\n(End of file - total 215 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Implementation Summary: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document summarizes the complete implementation of the K8s/AgentCube Provider system for the AgentCube CLI project, following the specifications in `proposal.md`.\n\n## Implemented Components\n\n### 1. Provider Base Interface (`agentcube/providers/base.py`)\n\n**Classes and Enums:**\n- `ProviderStatus` - Enumeration of provider states (pending, deploying, running, failed, not_found, error)\n- `DeploymentResult` - Dataclass for deployment operation results with `to_dict()` method\n- `AgentStatus` - Dataclass for agent status information with `to_dict()` method\n- `BaseProvider` - Abstract base class defining the provider interface\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `deploy(agent_name, image_url, port, **kwargs)` - Deploy an agent\n- `get_status(agent_name)` - Get agent status\n- `delete(agent_name)` - Delete an agent","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775876455436,"end":1775876455448}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876455453,"sessionID":"ses_285850964ffey2ZpSGUQcIATeP","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7c3bf1001WJ7kAD0qCTZ2ff","messageID":"msg_d7a7c2922001oWX4AMXbXb7DA7","sessionID":"ses_285850964ffey2ZpSGUQcIATeP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e72c8539f1994db3a435212671085522","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI\n2: \n3: A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\n4: \n5: ## Installation\n6: \n7: ```bash\n8: pip install agentcube\n9: ```\n10: \n11: Or install from source:\n12: \n13: ```bash\n14: cd cmd/cli\n15: pip install -e .\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Usage\n19: \n20: The CLI provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of AI agents.\n21: \n22: ### Pack Command\n23: \n24: Package an agent workspace by validating and preparing it:\n25: \n26: ```bash\n27: kubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n28: ```\n29: \n30: Options:\n31: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n32: - `--agent-name TEXT`: Override the agent name\n33: - `--language [python|java]`: Programming language\n34: - `--entrypoint TEXT`: Override the entrypoint command\n35: - `--port INTEGER`: Port to expose in the Dockerfile\n36: - `--build-mode [local|cloud]`: Build strategy\n37: - `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n38: - `--output PATH`: Output path for packaged workspace\n39: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n40: \n41: Example:\n42: \n43: ```bash\n44: kubectl-agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent --language python --port 8080\n45: ```\n46: \n47: ### Build Command\n48: \n49: Build a container image from the packaged agent workspace:\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: kubectl-agentcube build [OPTIONS]\n53: ```\n54: \n55: Options:\n56: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n57: - `-p, --proxy TEXT`: Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n58: - `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n59: - `--output PATH`: Output path for build artifacts\n60: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n61: \n62: Example:\n63: \n64: ```bash\n65: kubectl-agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### Publish Command\n69: \n70: Publish an agent to the specified provider:\n71: \n72: ```bash\n73: kubectl-agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n74: ```\n75: \n76: Options:\n77: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n78: - `--version TEXT`: Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n79: - `--image-url TEXT`: Image repository URL\n80: - `--image-username TEXT`: Username for image repository\n81: - `--image-password TEXT`: Password for image repository\n82: - `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n83: - `--region TEXT`: Deployment region\n84: - `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n85: - `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n86: - `--node-port INTEGER`: Specific NodePort for K8s deployment\n87: - `--replicas INTEGER`: Number of replicas for K8s deployment\n88: - `--namespace TEXT`: The namespace for the deployment\n89: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n90: \n91: Example:\n92: \n93: ```bash\n94: kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080 --replicas 3\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### Invoke Command\n98: \n99: Invoke a published agent with the given payload:\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 170. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI\n\nA developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube\n```\n\nOr install from source:\n\n```bash\ncd cmd/cli\npip install -e .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe CLI provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of AI agents.","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md","time":{"start":1775876455439,"end":1775876455450}}}}
